[normal]Commissioned rese[bold]arch[bold]Channel 4 recently undertook to educate itself 
[normal]more about the state of play of women’s sport in the UK
[normal], commissioning a private
[normal] external research project
[normal] 
[normal]on this issue for internal information purposes.
[normal]While recognising that there are reasons to be 
[normal]optimistic about women’s sport – such as the
[normal] impressive
[normal] peak audiences for women’s events at the Olympics and Paralympics and the increasing levels of sponsorship of female athletes at London 2012 – this research found that there are a number of wider deve
[normal]lopmental challenges that need to be tackled.
[normal]For example
[normal], while broadcast coverage may be a necessary condition for popularising women’s sport, it found that is not an exclusive one: many other factors are required to work as part of a virtuous cycle, as 
